t is Exempted or Waived? Required Documentation Submit to: Hazlewood Act         E A resident of Texas, entered service in Texas or claimed Texas as home of record per DD214 and is currently residing in Texas Received an honorable discharge or discharged under honorable conditions Served at least 181 days of active duty exclusive of training Have no State or State-guaranteed educational loans in default Other Federal veteran education benefits that are limited to payment of tuition and fees must be less than the value of the Hazlewood exemption Enrolled in classes for which the college receives tax support Satisfactory academic progress as determined by UNT System Tuition   Mandatory fees except Student Services Fee   Course Fees Completed Application Veterans DD214 Certificate of Eligibility for veterans discharged after 9/11/01 Registration in the Hazlewood online databaseStudent Accounting Hazlewood Specialists UNT Student Veteran Services Office Sage Hall Suite 123 Fax 940-369-5447 Hazlewood Legacy Act E The biological, adopted or step child of an eligible veteran or the veteran’s claimed dependent on the Federal Income Tax Return for the current year or the preceding year A resident of Texas 25 years old or younger on the first day of the semester for which the exemption is being claimed Enrolled in classes for which the college receives tax support Satisfactory academic progress as determined by UNT System Same as Hazlewood Act Completed Application Veterans DD214 Certificate of Eligibility for veterans discharged after 9/11/01 Relationship Documentation which can be birth certificate, adoption papers or transcript of recent income tax return reflecting dependency Registration in the Hazlewood online database Student Accounting Hazlewood Specialists UNT Student Veteran Services Office Sage Hall Suite 123 Fax 940-369-5447 Hazlewood Act for Spouse/Child E A resident of Texas The spouse or child of a veteran who, at the time of entry into the U.S. Armed Forces, w