rk in the semester the waiver is active For teaching employees, work directly w/ students in an academic environment at least 51% of their time Substitutes resident tuition for non-resident tuition Waiver Form (comes from employing department)   Official letter from the employing institution, if different from UNT, verifying that the employee meets their program eligibility requirements   For dependents, proof of relationship to qualifying employee UNT Graduate School Admissions Office Faculty and their Dependents   TEC Sec 54.211 W Professor at UNT or another Texas public institution Employed ½ time or more on a regular monthly salary basis Employed as of the:      12th class day of a long   semester      4th class day of a summer semester      2nd class day in a3 week session Substitutes resident tuition for non-resident tuition without regard to the length of time they have resided in Texas Waiver Form (comes from employing department) Official letter from the Director of Personnel at the employing institution, if different from UNT, verifying that the employee meets their eligibility requirements For dependents, proof of relationship to qualifying Faculty UNT Student Accounting and University Cashiering Services Senior Citizen   TEC Sec 54.365 E Must be 65 years of age or older Enrolled in classes for which the college receives tax support Must maintain a 2.0 GPA for undergraduate and a 3.0 GPA for Graduate or Post Baccalaureate to continue receiving exemption No Excessive hours per TEC Section 54.014 allowed for continuing students Tuition for up to 6 hours each semester Completed Application   Documentation of qualifying age UNT Student Accounting and University Cashiering Services Economic Development & Diversification   TEC Sec 54.222 W Student or student’s primary caretaker (must reside with student) establishes residence prior to  institution’s enrollment date as a result of employment in a business or organization that was established, not earlier than five years before enrollment date, as part of Texas’ economic development and diversification program Student files with institution a letter of intent to establish residency in Texas Substitutes resident for non-resident tuition and fees without having established residency per the Texas Education Code Certification of the eligibility of the business or organization Letter of intent to establish residency UNT Student Accounting and University Cashiering Services Children under Conservatorship of the Dept of Family and Protective Svcs   TEC Sec 54.366 E Texas Resident who is or has been in foster care or other residential care Enrolled in classes for which the college receives tax support Tuition and Fees Certificate of eligibility from the Tx Dept. of Family and Protective Services UNT Student Accounting and University Cashiering Services Children of Disabled or Deceased Firefighters & Law Enforcement Officers (includes Peace Officers, Game Wardens and Employees of Correctional Institutions)   TEC Sec 54.351 E Apply before the age of 21 Meet UNT Entrance Requirements Remain in Good Standing Begin term or session prior to 26th birthday Enrolled in classes for which the college receives tax support Maintain a 2.0 GPA for undergraduate and a 3.0 GPA for Graduate or Post Baccalaureate to continue receiving exemption No Excessive hours per TEC Section 54.014 allowed for continuing students Tuition and Fees for the first 120 undergraduate semester credit hours for which the person registers   Excludes: Property Deposit Late Fees Rental Fees       Certificate from the Texas Higher Education Coordinating Board   Student must inform Student Accounting and University Cashiering Services of their enrollment each semester. UNT Student Accounting and University Cashiering Services   Adopted Students formerly in Foster Care or Other Residential Care (Adoption)   TEC Sec 54.367 E Texas Resident who is or has been in foster care or other residential care Adopted and the subject of a