 Copy of Passport Photo/Information Page Copy of Visa (If the student has not yet been issued a visa, the student should indicate the type of visa on the Mexican Waiver application form) Statement of Financial Need UNT International Office Competitive Scholarship   TEC Sec 54.213 W Non-resident  Awarded a scholarship(s) by UNT in competition with other students, both resident and non-resident, totaling $1,000 or more Substitutes resident for non-resident tuition and fees without having established residency per the Texas Education Code Cannot exceed 12 months Form must be completed by the academic department and forwarded to Student Financial Aid and Scholarships Student Financial Aid & Scholarships Clinical Nurse Preceptors and their Children   TEC SEC 54.356 E Texas Resident Registered Nurse or Child of Qualifying Nurse Preceptor Serves under a preceptor agreement w/in an undergraduate professional nursing program as a clinical preceptor for enrolled students Enrolled in classes for which the college receives tax support Maintain a 2.0 GPA for undergraduate and a 3.0 GPA for Graduate or Post Baccalaureate to continue receiving exemption No Excessive hours per TEC Section 54.014 allowed for continuing students Does Not Include: Individuals with a baccalaureate degree or individuals who have received this exemption for 10 semesters or summer sessions at an institution(s) of higher education   $500 or tuition amount whichever is less Completed Application   Written proof of eligibility from the Nursing department through which the Preceptor has or had a written preceptor agreement UNT Student Accounting and University Cashiering Services Texas Tomorrow Fund/ Texas Guaranteed Tuition Plan W Must use fund to cover tuition and mandatory fees for the semester Substitutes resident for non-resident tuition and fees without having established residency per the Texas Education Code Copy of Texas Tomorrow Fund/ Texas Guaranteed Tuition Plan card UNT Student Accounting and Uni